Date: 1/8/1895
Source: Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: people join the Waikoikoi Arbor Association by "paying to thetreasurer a 'colonial Robert', or, in the vulgar tongue, by 'bobbing it'.It is expected that the treasurer will be handsomely 'bobbed'."
Notes: This suggests a use of "bob" (for shilling) in a verbal sense which has notbeen noted in the dictionary.Otautau is near Riverton; Waikoikoi is near Gore
